00:14:46.920 --> 00:14:48.950
So again,
my goal here is to help you make a

00:14:48.970 --> 00:14:52.440
good decision if you're considering
freemium as your business model.

00:14:52.440 --> 00:14:55.520
To help you do so,
we've developed a framework that involves

00:14:55.710 --> 00:14:57.210
three questions that you should consider.

00:14:57.210 --> 00:15:01.820
The first, what are your target
market's expectations?

00:15:01.820 --> 00:15:06.150
So what I mean here is from
a business model perspective,

00:15:06.410 --> 00:15:09.680
don't try to fit a square
peg into a round hole.

00:15:09.790 --> 00:15:12.850
To explain what I mean,
let me walk you through a few examples.

00:15:12.850 --> 00:15:14.440
So let's take Scrabble.

00:15:14.440 --> 00:15:19.310
Scrabble is a brand that has existed
in the physical world for many,

00:15:19.310 --> 00:15:20.400
many decades.

00:15:20.430 --> 00:15:24.470
The target market expectations
for a brand like Scrabble are

00:15:24.680 --> 00:15:26.370
that it's a premium product.

00:15:26.520 --> 00:15:30.360
You pay a single price and you can
play Scrabble as many times as you

00:15:30.820 --> 00:15:33.160
want with as many people as you want.

00:15:33.160 --> 00:15:37.600
In contrast, if you look at racing games
or time management games,

00:15:37.600 --> 00:15:41.280
there are expectations among
gamers of those types of games

00:15:41.280 --> 00:15:45.460
that through skill and experience,
they can acquire enhancements

00:15:45.460 --> 00:15:46.440
or expand their game.

00:15:46.520 --> 00:15:51.060
So make sure your business
model fits with what your

00:15:51.080 --> 00:15:53.870
target market might expect.

00:15:54.260 --> 00:15:56.800
As we walk through this discussion,
let's take a look at the

00:15:56.800 --> 00:15:58.140
funnel for downloads.

00:15:58.260 --> 00:16:00.300
So at the top, you see downloads.

00:16:00.350 --> 00:16:01.620
This is your target market.

00:16:01.770 --> 00:16:06.120
Being free will not make everyone
in the world download your app,

00:16:06.120 --> 00:16:10.000
but it may expand your reach
within your target market.

00:16:11.450 --> 00:16:14.640
The next question in the
framework is can you segment the

00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:16.540
experience between free and paid?

00:16:16.540 --> 00:16:20.490
If as a developer running a
business you decide that you're not

00:16:20.810 --> 00:16:24.250
interested in acquiring free users,
that's completely fine.

00:16:24.260 --> 00:16:26.800
Just don't choose freemium as your model.

00:16:26.800 --> 00:16:31.070
The most successful freemium products
and apps and games in the store are

00:16:31.550 --> 00:16:35.250
providing a tremendous amount of
value to both free and paid users.

00:16:35.260 --> 00:16:38.530
The reason why is that the
path to monetization in

00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:41.010
freemium is through engagement.

00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:45.830
And if you throw up a paywall as
soon as a user launches your game,

00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:50.200
you're not giving them a chance to get
engaged and you're not giving yourselves

00:16:50.330 --> 00:16:52.500
a chance to monetize that customer.

00:16:55.500 --> 00:16:58.240
So the next piece of
the funnel is retention.

00:16:58.280 --> 00:17:02.680
This is the percent of your target market
that is getting some kind of value out

00:17:02.680 --> 00:17:05.830
of your product and continues to use it.

00:17:06.890 --> 00:17:09.100
So before I move on to the
final question in the framework,

00:17:09.100 --> 00:17:12.770
let's take a look at the typical
game loop for a freemium game.

00:17:12.770 --> 00:17:14.780
At the top, you see action.

00:17:14.780 --> 00:17:17.790
This is winning a battle
or winning a race.

00:17:17.790 --> 00:17:18.950
Next, you see reward.

00:17:18.980 --> 00:17:21.660
Typically in freemium products,
this is currency.

00:17:21.660 --> 00:17:25.310
And then you see expansion,
which is you use that currency

00:17:25.430 --> 00:17:28.470
to buy a new car or expand,
buy new tires or buy new

00:17:28.580 --> 00:17:30.410
weapons for your battle.

00:17:30.420 --> 00:17:33.720
So what's important,
and the reason I'm sharing this with you

00:17:33.820 --> 00:17:36.780
today is to be successful in freemium,
it is very important to

00:17:36.780 --> 00:17:36.780
be successful in freemium.

00:17:36.800 --> 00:17:40.810
It is very important that you allow
progression through this game loop

00:17:40.860 --> 00:17:42.830
without requiring users to pay.

00:17:42.840 --> 00:17:47.030
That might be a hard thing for people
to swallow if you're running a business,

00:17:47.030 --> 00:17:50.630
but again, then freemium might not be
the right model for you.

00:17:51.590 --> 00:17:56.870
So the last piece of the framework is do
you have a plan to create lasting value?

00:17:57.240 --> 00:17:58.340
This is twofold.

00:17:58.340 --> 00:18:03.410
This is your plan as a developer
to have a rich plan for updates,

00:18:03.410 --> 00:18:06.000
content and features updates over time.

00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:09.270
And this also relates to the
inherent value of the product itself.

00:18:09.280 --> 00:18:13.850
If you're building something that only
has 30 minutes or one hour of gameplay,

00:18:13.940 --> 00:18:17.200
there's probably not any
lasting value in that for users.

00:18:17.200 --> 00:18:20.300
So freemium is probably not
the right model for you.

00:18:23.500 --> 00:18:24.650
Which brings us to the
last piece of the funnel,

00:18:24.650 --> 00:18:26.220
which is conversion.

00:18:26.260 --> 00:18:30.510
The percent of those who have retained,
who've decided to pay.

00:18:30.680 --> 00:18:31.800
So do the math.

00:18:31.900 --> 00:18:34.530
It's incredibly important to
determining whether freemium

00:18:34.580 --> 00:18:35.640
is the right model for you.

00:18:35.900 --> 00:18:39.480
If you have a niche game,
you might see a higher retention and a

00:18:39.480 --> 00:18:44.030
higher conversion and a higher average
spread so the math can work out for you.

00:18:44.400 --> 00:18:46.100
Or in contrast,
if you're building something

00:18:46.100 --> 00:18:48.950
with broad market appeal,
you might see millions

00:18:49.000 --> 00:18:51.960
and millions of downloads,
but maybe a lower retention,

00:18:51.960 --> 00:18:55.260
lower conversion, lower average spread,
but the math can still work out

00:18:55.260 --> 00:18:57.320
because the numbers are so big.

00:18:57.400 --> 00:19:01.500
So start with your target market and
do the math from that point forward.

00:19:01.590 --> 00:19:03.750
So you've gone through the framework,
you've done the math,

00:19:03.750 --> 00:19:05.860
and you've decided that
freemium is right for you.

00:19:05.860 --> 00:19:08.020
So what are the next steps?

00:19:08.170 --> 00:19:12.820
So again, first,
identify and focus on your target market.

00:19:13.010 --> 00:19:16.170
Have a business model that's
consistent with what your

00:19:16.170 --> 00:19:18.110
target market might expect.

00:19:18.290 --> 00:19:22.830
Next, prioritize engagement
before monetization.

00:19:23.150 --> 00:19:27.190
You're not doing yourself any
service if you throw up a paywall as

00:19:27.260 --> 00:19:28.760
soon as a user launches your game.

00:19:28.760 --> 00:19:30.800
Give them a chance to get engaged.

00:19:30.800 --> 00:19:33.910
Give them a chance to find
some value out of your product.

00:19:35.750 --> 00:19:40.200
Incorporate the business model into the
early stages of your product design.

00:19:40.200 --> 00:19:43.840
If you've built something great
and beautiful without any regard

00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:47.410
for the business model and at the
11th hour right before you launch,

00:19:47.500 --> 00:19:50.580
you put an in-app store in there,
it's not going to feel native or

00:19:50.580 --> 00:19:54.720
natural to customers and chances are,
again, they're not going to get engaged.

00:19:54.750 --> 00:19:56.900
So consider the business
model from the very,

00:19:56.990 --> 00:19:58.940
very beginning of your product design.

00:20:00.320 --> 00:20:01.640
Track your metrics.

00:20:01.650 --> 00:20:06.990
And the takeaway here is don't be afraid
to tune your economy if freemium is right

00:20:07.120 --> 00:20:08.720
for you or freemium is not right for you.

00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:11.760
Don't be afraid to switch to
a different business model.

00:20:13.470 --> 00:20:14.840
Treat your game as a service.

00:20:14.840 --> 00:20:18.230
The most successful freemium games
in the store really are treated

00:20:18.240 --> 00:20:22.560
as services by their developers
with constant live updates and

00:20:22.560 --> 00:20:25.890
really endless amounts of value,
entertainment value that gamers

00:20:25.890 --> 00:20:27.400
can get from their products.

00:20:42.220 --> 00:20:43.510
And then lastly,
protect and respect our mutual customers.

00:20:43.510 --> 00:20:44.710
When I say protect our customers,
if you're building a game

00:20:44.710 --> 00:20:45.980
targeted towards kids,
put yourself in the parents' shoes.

00:20:45.980 --> 00:20:47.130
Consider A,
whether freemium's right to begin with,

00:20:47.130 --> 00:20:48.170
but if it is,
consider the number of in-app SKUs you

00:20:48.190 --> 00:20:49.580
might make available and consider
whether you need that $99 in-app

00:20:49.690 --> 00:20:50.620
SKU in your kids-focused product.

00:20:51.310 --> 00:20:53.510
And then when I talk about
respecting customers,

00:20:53.650 --> 00:20:55.480
this ties back to what I've been saying.

00:20:55.830 --> 00:20:57.410
Give them a chance to get engaged.

00:20:57.830 --> 00:21:02.290
Don't put a paywall in front of them
as soon as they launch your product.

00:21:02.700 --> 00:21:04.260
So that's my discussion on freemium.

00:21:04.270 --> 00:21:06.600
Next, we'll talk about pricing.

00:21:06.720 --> 00:21:08.710
So the App Store runs
under the agency model,

00:21:08.830 --> 00:21:13.140
which means that you as a developer have
sole control over the price of your app.

00:21:13.140 --> 00:21:14.590
Our guidance here is twofold.

00:21:14.840 --> 00:21:17.430
Price thoughtfully and take
a look at the competition.

00:21:17.490 --> 00:21:21.460
If you're building a casual game that's
meant to compete with Angry Birds and

00:21:21.460 --> 00:21:25.240
you want to charge $5 or $10 for it,
chances are you're probably not

00:21:25.240 --> 00:21:29.940
going to do well because the market
for that type of game is $0.99.

00:21:29.940 --> 00:21:34.180
The other key takeaway here is
that there's a misconception out

00:21:34.190 --> 00:21:37.620
there in the market that the only
two price points that work in

00:21:37.630 --> 00:21:40.480
the App Store are free and $0.99.

00:21:40.480 --> 00:21:42.400
And again, as someone who looks
at this data every day,

00:21:42.400 --> 00:21:45.450
I can tell you that that's
just flat out not true.

00:21:45.680 --> 00:21:48.060
We see many,
many developers of apps and games

00:21:48.440 --> 00:21:51.750
seeing success at higher price points.

00:21:51.940 --> 00:21:55.860
Next, consider price promotions, sales.

00:21:55.910 --> 00:21:56.930
Don't do them all the time.

00:21:56.930 --> 00:22:01.130
If you do, customers will constantly be
waiting for that next deal and

00:22:01.150 --> 00:22:02.860
they'll never buy your product.

00:22:02.930 --> 00:22:06.290
But well-timed price promotions
are a great way to grow your

00:22:06.290 --> 00:22:07.980
business on the App Store.

00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:11.740
So a couple last steps before you launch.

00:22:11.740 --> 00:22:14.900
First, communicate with Apple.

00:22:14.900 --> 00:22:18.040
As I said before,
there's thousands and thousands

00:22:18.050 --> 00:22:20.580
of new apps added to the
App Store on a weekly basis.

00:22:20.580 --> 00:22:22.810
If you've built something
you're proud of,

00:22:22.810 --> 00:22:25.370
that you think we should
tell our customers about,

00:22:25.520 --> 00:22:27.170
it always helps to let us know.

00:22:27.170 --> 00:22:31.240
So that first email address,
appstorepromotionatapple.com,

00:22:31.240 --> 00:22:33.560
is something monitored by my team.

00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:36.930
Tell us who you are, what you've built,
and why you think our customers

00:22:36.930 --> 00:22:39.380
would enjoy your product,
and we'll take a look.

00:22:40.130 --> 00:22:43.700
The second email address,
appoftheweekatapple.com,

00:22:43.700 --> 00:22:47.640
if you have a well-localized paid
product that you'd like to nominate

00:22:47.900 --> 00:22:50.610
for our App of the Week program,
please send us your information

00:22:50.610 --> 00:22:52.130
at appoftheweekatapple.com.

00:22:52.220 --> 00:22:53.610
We'll take a look as well.

00:22:54.860 --> 00:22:58.190
Next, plan for app review to take time.

00:22:58.420 --> 00:23:00.820
Gone are the days of app
review taking weeks and weeks.

00:23:00.820 --> 00:23:05.400
Our published guidance these days is
that roughly 95% of apps are reviewed

00:23:05.620 --> 00:23:07.880
within five business days or less.

00:23:07.880 --> 00:23:11.110
That being said,
it's better to be safe than sorry.

00:23:11.110 --> 00:23:13.780
So plan for at least
two weeks in app review,

00:23:13.780 --> 00:23:17.260
just in case last minute bug
pops up or you have issues with

00:23:17.260 --> 00:23:21.320
launching your marketing campaign,
things of that nature.

00:23:21.320 --> 00:23:24.540
And then the last point here,
my colleague Steve will talk

00:23:24.540 --> 00:23:26.160
about in further detail.

00:23:26.160 --> 00:23:29.510
Don't rely on your chances
of being featured by the

00:23:29.510 --> 00:23:31.490
App Store as your marketing plan.

00:23:31.490 --> 00:23:33.300
There are many,
many things you can do that

00:23:33.300 --> 00:23:34.540
are within your control.

00:23:34.540 --> 00:23:38.260
And as I said, Steve will talk about that
more in just a few minutes.

00:23:38.260 --> 00:23:40.260
So you've launched your product.

00:23:40.450 --> 00:23:40.910
Now what?

00:23:41.340 --> 00:23:44.890
Well, first and foremost,
monitor your ratings and reviews.

00:23:44.910 --> 00:23:47.700
App Store customers are incredibly vocal.

00:23:47.700 --> 00:23:49.700
They'll tell you what you're doing well.

00:23:49.700 --> 00:23:51.280
They'll tell you what you're not doing.

00:23:51.280 --> 00:23:51.280
So you've launched your product.

00:23:51.280 --> 00:23:51.280
Now what?

00:23:51.280 --> 00:23:51.280
Well, first and foremost,
monitor your ratings and reviews.

00:23:51.280 --> 00:23:51.280
App Store customers are incredibly vocal.

00:23:51.280 --> 00:23:51.280
They'll tell you what you're doing well.

00:23:51.280 --> 00:23:51.300
They'll tell you what
you're not doing well.

00:23:51.300 --> 00:23:56.150
You may discover some bugs and you may
get some great ideas for future updates.

00:23:58.080 --> 00:24:01.910
Speaking of updates,
launching it and leaving it is not a

00:24:01.910 --> 00:24:03.820
strategy for success in the App Store.

00:24:03.820 --> 00:24:05.510
The market is too competitive.

00:24:05.520 --> 00:24:08.040
Here's some real data
from Clash of Clans.

00:24:08.040 --> 00:24:12.380
Each orange star represents a significant
update they've made to the product.

00:24:12.450 --> 00:24:15.150
I had to remove the scale
for confidentiality purposes,

00:24:15.220 --> 00:24:18.500
but I'm sure you all are aware that
this game is pretty successful.

00:24:18.570 --> 00:24:22.020
What's interesting to note are
not just the spikes that they

00:24:22.180 --> 00:24:25.860
saw when they updated their game,
but in between the updates,

00:24:25.860 --> 00:24:28.760
there's some flatness
and even in some cases,

00:24:28.770 --> 00:24:29.710
some decline.

00:24:29.840 --> 00:24:33.920
So well-timed updates are a great
way to build momentum in the store.

00:24:33.980 --> 00:24:38.660
Test your apps thoroughly so you
can avoid constant bug fix updates,

00:24:38.730 --> 00:24:42.330
but the right timing for feature-rich
or content-rich updates is

00:24:42.400 --> 00:24:44.080
roughly every four to six weeks.

00:24:45.890 --> 00:24:48.900
Next, use push notifications and sharing.

00:24:48.900 --> 00:24:52.500
On the left,
you see push notification screen.

00:24:52.500 --> 00:24:56.180
Avoid using notifications in a way
that might be perceived as spam

00:24:56.180 --> 00:24:59.040
or marketing by our customers,
but well-timed,

00:24:59.040 --> 00:25:02.350
well-written push notifications
are a great way to bring

00:25:02.780 --> 00:25:04.400
people back to your product.

00:25:04.460 --> 00:25:07.670
And then on the right,
if people love using your game and

00:25:07.760 --> 00:25:12.300
they're proud of their accomplishments,
use our share sheet functionality

00:25:12.300 --> 00:25:15.160
and make it easy for them
to tell others about it.

00:25:17.260 --> 00:25:19.590
Next, monitor your sales and trends.

00:25:20.000 --> 00:25:22.100
This might seem obvious,
but you'd be surprised at how

00:25:22.100 --> 00:25:24.100
many people don't do this.

00:25:24.220 --> 00:25:26.900
There's a wealth of data available
to you in iTunes Connect.

00:25:27.060 --> 00:25:30.920
There's a vibrant ecosystem of third
parties whose existence is to help

00:25:31.000 --> 00:25:33.160
you optimize your business on iOS.

00:25:33.160 --> 00:25:37.690
You never know what you might discover,
especially a market where you didn't

00:25:37.750 --> 00:25:41.940
think your app was doing well in,
but it is, and there's a great idea for

00:25:41.940 --> 00:25:45.640
a future update to add the
localization for that market.

00:25:47.100 --> 00:25:48.780
So that's my discussion
on best practices.

00:25:48.980 --> 00:25:51.250
Next, we'll talk a little
bit about localization.

00:25:51.280 --> 00:25:54.610
So as I said before,
the App Store is a global business

00:25:54.640 --> 00:25:56.940
in 155 countries around the world.

00:25:56.940 --> 00:26:00.320
So as a developer,
you need to think globally.

00:26:00.320 --> 00:26:03.520
There really is an unprecedented
opportunity for you to acquire

00:26:03.570 --> 00:26:06.640
customers from all corners of the globe.

00:26:06.660 --> 00:26:08.300
But one size doesn't fit all.

00:26:08.300 --> 00:26:12.720
There's lots of cultural and linguistic
differences from country to country.

00:26:13.400 --> 00:26:16.340
So to be successful,
you need to not only think globally,

00:26:16.340 --> 00:26:17.790
but you need to be local.

00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:21.080
And what I mean by that is to localize.

