00:27:58.950 --> 00:28:00.640
could track their progress.

00:28:00.650 --> 00:28:04.790
And while culturalization doesn't
necessarily apply to every game,

00:28:04.790 --> 00:28:08.460
where there's a fit,
it will absolutely make a difference.

00:28:10.520 --> 00:28:13.150
So that's culturalization.

00:28:13.310 --> 00:28:15.260
So languages.

00:28:15.380 --> 00:28:19.000
Here's the list of recommended
languages for localization if you have

00:28:19.000 --> 00:28:21.640
something that's globally relevant.

00:28:21.710 --> 00:28:24.340
English, French, Italian, German,
and Spanish.

00:28:24.390 --> 00:28:27.320
The Asian languages,
traditional and simplified Chinese,

00:28:27.520 --> 00:28:29.260
Japanese, and Korean.

00:28:29.330 --> 00:28:32.250
Brazilian, Portuguese, Russian, Turkish,
and Arabic.

00:28:32.310 --> 00:28:35.270
This is not prioritized,
but this is the group of languages

00:28:35.330 --> 00:28:39.900
that we recommend you start with if
you have a globally relevant product.

00:28:41.620 --> 00:28:44.600
So let's look at some more data
to show you that localization

00:28:44.710 --> 00:28:46.660
actually does have an impact.

00:28:46.700 --> 00:28:50.540
Again, we thank Supercell for letting
us share this data with you.

00:28:50.590 --> 00:28:54.080
This is Clash of Clans and
their Chinese localization.

