A little bit of growth,
not doing quite as well

00:29:15.660 --> 00:29:18.600
as they were in China,
but massive growth when they tune

00:29:18.720 --> 00:29:21.500
their product for the Japanese market.

00:29:23.810 --> 00:29:25.400
And let's take a look at the charts.

00:29:25.470 --> 00:29:27.650
Here's a recent screenshot
of the charts from China,

00:29:27.700 --> 00:29:29.200
Japan, and France.

00:29:29.300 --> 00:29:33.590
With all but two exceptions here,
Angry Birds and Clash of Clans

00:29:33.600 --> 00:29:36.130
that have gone the branding
route with their app name,

00:29:36.130 --> 00:29:39.850
not their full apps, just the app name,
every app you see at the top

00:29:39.910 --> 00:29:43.230
of the charts here is localized
for these individual markets.

00:29:43.270 --> 00:29:46.810
And on top of that,
our local editors in these markets

00:29:46.810 --> 00:29:51.090
have a very strong preference
for promoting localized apps.

00:29:51.730 --> 00:29:54.900
So again, think globally, but be local.

00:29:54.940 --> 00:29:57.900
And Apple provides a number of
resources to help you to do so.

00:29:58.120 --> 00:29:59.280
There's the URL at the top.

00:29:59.320 --> 00:30:02.630
You'll find some tips and tricks
for localization on this page,

00:30:02.650 --> 00:30:06.250
as well as a list of third-party
localization vendors if you don't

00:30:06.440 --> 00:30:10.800
have the linguistic expertise in-house
to localize into dozens of languages.

00:30:12.630 --> 00:30:14.940
So that's my talk on localization.

00:30:14.940 --> 00:30:16.740
And last but not least, getting featured.

00:30:18.780 --> 00:30:21.840
So first and foremost,
focus on what you can control,

00:30:21.860 --> 00:30:26.620
and that's building something great
and unique that our customers love.

00:30:26.630 --> 00:30:29.510
Next, have a strong App Store presence.

00:30:29.700 --> 00:30:31.320
These things matter.

00:30:31.320 --> 00:30:35.420
We put our stamp of approval on
apps and games that we feature,

00:30:35.440 --> 00:30:39.410
and you should well represent who you
are and what you've built and make a

00:30:39.410 --> 00:30:42.760
strong introduction to our customers.

00:30:42.810 --> 00:30:46.150
Choose the right business
model and price thoughtfully.

00:30:46.780 --> 00:30:50.550
Offer customers a universal binary.

00:30:50.610 --> 00:30:52.600
Localize in relevant markets.

00:30:52.650 --> 00:30:55.300
And lastly,
communicate with the App Store team.

00:30:57.850 --> 00:30:59.080
So that's my talk for today.

00:30:59.080 --> 00:31:00.100
Thank you very much.

00:31:00.250 --> 00:31:01.780
And now I'll turn it
over to my colleague,

00:31:01.830 --> 00:31:04.640
Steve McGuigan,
to talk about App Store marketing.

00:31:10.370 --> 00:31:11.440
Good afternoon.

00:31:11.720 --> 00:31:16.280
My name is Steve McGuigan and I look
after marketing for the App Store.

00:31:16.330 --> 00:31:19.780
You know, we spend a lot of time thinking
about apps at Apple and

00:31:19.780 --> 00:31:23.080
not just on the App Store,
but Apple as a whole.

00:31:23.190 --> 00:31:26.340
And we love marketing apps
through our many channels.

00:31:26.400 --> 00:31:29.860
Many of the apps come from some
of the audience members here.

00:31:29.860 --> 00:31:32.740
The channels we market
through are television,

00:31:32.820 --> 00:31:33.470
print.

00:31:33.470 --> 00:31:38.550
You'll see us marketing apps on
billboards throughout cities.

00:31:39.610 --> 00:31:44.140
We market apps through our over 400
retail locations around the globe and

00:31:44.140 --> 00:31:46.980
our thousands of channel partners.

00:31:47.820 --> 00:31:53.000
We spend a lot of time and energy
marketing apps on apple.com,

00:31:53.010 --> 00:31:55.650
as well as to the hundreds of
millions of emails that we send out

00:31:55.650 --> 00:31:58.510
to our customers on a monthly basis.

00:31:58.790 --> 00:32:01.710
And then finally,
we speak to nearly 11 million

00:32:01.800 --> 00:32:05.290
fans and followers on social
media every single day.

00:32:06.760 --> 00:32:09.320
But as Alex said earlier,
you control much of your

00:32:09.350 --> 00:32:11.320
success on the App Store.

00:32:11.370 --> 00:32:14.500
You are not dependent
upon getting featured.

00:32:14.880 --> 00:32:18.410
Your success, of course,
starts with a great app,

00:32:18.410 --> 00:32:21.640
but that success will be propelled
by having a great marketing plan.

00:32:21.640 --> 00:32:25.350
And that's what I'm here
to talk to you about today.

00:32:25.540 --> 00:32:28.370
I'm going to begin by talking about
three programs that we've created

00:32:28.750 --> 00:32:33.220
to help you not only monetize,
but also help you promote your apps.

00:32:33.260 --> 00:32:35.720
I'll talk about some of the resources
we've made available to you to

00:32:35.860 --> 00:32:37.080
make your marketing look great.

00:32:37.310 --> 00:32:40.910
And then I'll conclude by talking
about the components that make up

00:32:40.960 --> 00:32:43.410
a comprehensive marketing campaign.

00:32:44.030 --> 00:32:46.780
So let's begin with the
programs and resources.

00:32:46.830 --> 00:32:50.490
I've been hearing for quite some time
that developers have been looking for

00:32:50.490 --> 00:32:56.000
a way for them to market their apps
to customers for free without making

00:32:56.510 --> 00:32:58.380
their app free on the App Store.

00:32:58.500 --> 00:33:01.460
So I'm proud to announce a
new program that we're calling

00:33:01.600 --> 00:33:03.350
the App Store Code Program.

00:33:03.960 --> 00:33:06.480
This program will provide you,
the developer,

00:33:06.480 --> 00:33:12.700
the ability to market free offers to your
customers by using unique 12-digit codes.

00:33:14.470 --> 00:33:17.200
Currently,
the program is focused on offering

00:33:17.200 --> 00:33:20.120
your paid apps downloaded for free.

00:33:20.820 --> 00:33:23.290
Now, these are different than those
100 promo codes that you can

00:33:23.290 --> 00:33:24.490
request out of iTunes Connect.

00:33:24.550 --> 00:33:27.020
Those should be used
for your PR purposes,

00:33:27.250 --> 00:33:28.120
which I'll talk about later.

00:33:28.120 --> 00:33:30.460
These codes will come
in a much higher volume,

00:33:30.460 --> 00:33:33.360
and they should be used for
large marketing campaigns.

00:33:35.310 --> 00:33:37.390
Now it's a completely free program.

00:33:37.510 --> 00:33:42.030
You as the developer would waive
your 70% royalties and we as

00:33:42.030 --> 00:33:44.990
Apple would waive our 30% commission.

00:33:45.560 --> 00:33:48.040
And when you receive these codes,
you can distribute them

00:33:48.040 --> 00:33:50.020
digitally or physically.

00:33:50.020 --> 00:33:53.590
And I'll provide some examples
for you in a few slides.

00:33:54.430 --> 00:33:57.430
So let's first talk about
the benefits of this program.

00:33:57.570 --> 00:34:00.780
First,
you will be able to create an impactful

00:34:01.120 --> 00:34:03.830
and a high-value marketing promotion.

00:34:04.030 --> 00:34:07.490
It will not only aid in user acquisition,
but it also can be used in

00:34:07.490 --> 00:34:10.810
an engagement tool with some
of your existing customers.

00:34:11.100 --> 00:34:14.210
The beauty of this is
that it's built into iOS.

00:34:14.210 --> 00:34:18.290
So the redemption flow is simple,
frictionless, and will produce a

00:34:18.290 --> 00:34:20.400
consistent user experience.

00:34:21.820 --> 00:34:23.800
So let me get into a couple of
examples for you so you can understand

00:34:23.800 --> 00:34:26.150
how these codes can work for you.

00:34:26.250 --> 00:34:29.640
And the first is a digital
distribution example from our

00:34:29.870 --> 00:34:32.790
friends at Big Fish Games.

00:34:33.460 --> 00:34:36.820
They have a paid app called Fairway
Solitaire and they wanted to do a

00:34:36.820 --> 00:34:40.800
marketing campaign targeted at golf
enthusiasts and game enthusiasts.

00:34:40.800 --> 00:34:43.930
So they created this banner
or this ad that they presented

00:34:43.930 --> 00:34:47.800
through various mobile sites
addressing that targeted audience.

00:34:48.460 --> 00:34:51.460
The customer would see the ad
and they would tap on get it free

00:34:51.460 --> 00:34:54.800
where they'd be presented with
this terms and conditions page.

00:34:55.370 --> 00:34:56.800
But Big Fish had a great idea.

00:34:56.800 --> 00:34:59.850
They said, why don't we leverage this
opportunity to share this

00:34:59.850 --> 00:35:01.700
promotion through social networks?

00:35:01.800 --> 00:35:04.460
So they give the customer
the ability to go share this

00:35:04.460 --> 00:35:06.230
through Facebook and Twitter.

00:35:06.550 --> 00:35:08.730
But back to the redemption flow.

00:35:08.920 --> 00:35:11.540
The customer would tap on
the "Get it free" button,

00:35:11.660 --> 00:35:14.400
at which point the App Store would
launch automatically,

00:35:14.410 --> 00:35:18.170
and the customer would just
simply type in their password.

00:35:18.620 --> 00:35:22.640
That 12-digit code is automatically
populated into the redeem field.

00:35:22.700 --> 00:35:25.640
So all the customer needs to
do at this point is tap redeem

00:35:26.010 --> 00:35:26.960
and the app begins to download.

00:35:26.960 --> 00:35:29.500
A very simple experience
for the customer.

00:35:32.520 --> 00:35:34.600
But you also have an opportunity to
distribute these codes and activate

00:35:34.600 --> 00:35:37.570
your customers at a physical location.

00:35:37.570 --> 00:35:40.440
And Halfbrick came to us,
the makers of Fruit Ninja,

00:35:40.620 --> 00:35:41.460
and they had a great idea.

00:35:42.310 --> 00:35:45.730
They wanted to celebrate the anniversary
of Fruit Ninja and they thought they

00:35:45.730 --> 00:35:49.390
would produce a high quality event in
public venues throughout Australia.

00:35:50.200 --> 00:35:53.350
So the idea they came to us
with was they'll create a kiosk,

00:35:53.350 --> 00:35:56.470
it would have eight iPads around it,
a few flat screens,

00:35:56.470 --> 00:35:59.340
and customers could come
up and play Fruit Ninja.

00:36:00.400 --> 00:36:03.850
They would put signage out about town
driving people to this event and they

00:36:03.980 --> 00:36:07.360
would keep track of the high scores
that day as they were trying to find

00:36:07.360 --> 00:36:09.500
Australia's next Fruit Ninja master.

00:36:10.330 --> 00:36:15.030
Well, they took it a step further and
created four of these kiosks and placed

00:36:15.330 --> 00:36:20.320
these in shopping malls and parks
around Melbourne and Sydney recently.

00:36:21.220 --> 00:36:24.100
And while customers were
engaging with Fruit Ninja,

00:36:24.270 --> 00:36:27.450
they would provide them a physical
card and each card had its own

00:36:27.630 --> 00:36:29.370
unique 12-digit code on it.

00:36:30.180 --> 00:36:32.360
On the back, it explained how to redeem.

00:36:32.490 --> 00:36:35.500
It said, launch the app store,
plug in your password,

00:36:35.500 --> 00:36:39.540
type in that 12-digit code that
you saw on the front of the card,

00:36:39.600 --> 00:36:40.500
and tap redeem.

00:36:40.500 --> 00:36:43.810
And your app then downloads for free.

00:36:44.300 --> 00:37:04.000
[ Transcript missing ]

00:37:04.650 --> 00:37:08.750
We want to make sure that it's a great
experience for our mutual customers,

00:37:08.810 --> 00:37:10.800
so the offer needs to be open.

00:37:10.840 --> 00:37:13.470
In other words,
you can't require somebody to

00:37:13.470 --> 00:37:16.420
pay for these codes that you're
eventually giving away for free,

00:37:16.420 --> 00:37:20.480
or you can't require them to give you
a mailing address or an email address.

00:37:20.480 --> 00:37:24.180
We want it to be a delightful
experience for everybody.

00:37:26.700 --> 00:37:26.800
We'd ask that you track
your distribution.

00:37:26.840 --> 00:37:30.430
We'd like to know how many codes
you're putting through which channels.

00:37:30.430 --> 00:37:33.090
And then, of course, you would need our
approval to move forward.

00:37:33.200 --> 00:37:34.700
So how do you do that?

00:37:35.520 --> 00:37:36.700
Well, it's quite simple.

00:37:36.760 --> 00:37:40.700
Send us an email at
appstorecodes@apple.com.

00:37:40.700 --> 00:37:42.650
We will send you back a template.

00:37:42.780 --> 00:37:44.630
We'll ask you to fill out that
will describe the campaign

00:37:44.650 --> 00:37:47.700
that you're hoping to run,
which countries you want to run it in,

00:37:47.700 --> 00:37:49.560
what kind of distribution you want to do.

00:37:50.450 --> 00:37:52.530
And once we approve that,
we'll send you an

00:37:52.560 --> 00:37:53.920
agreement that you sign.

00:37:53.920 --> 00:37:57.700
You send us the agreement back,
and then we'll deliver you the codes.

00:37:58.360 --> 00:38:02.420
Now, one of the great benefits of this is
that you can track your redemptions in

00:38:02.440 --> 00:38:06.580
the Sales and Trends Report that you
already look at through iTunes Connect.

00:38:06.780 --> 00:38:09.280
So you can see the performance
of your campaign and the

00:38:09.280 --> 00:38:10.670
results on a daily basis.

00:38:11.660 --> 00:38:14.290
So that's our new App Store Code Program.

00:38:17.410 --> 00:38:18.740
The second program I want
to discuss with you is iAd.

00:38:18.780 --> 00:38:21.550
As you likely know,
iAd is Apple's digital

00:38:21.600 --> 00:38:23.440
advertising platform.

00:38:23.500 --> 00:38:28.820
And we know that you spend an enormous
amount of time producing great games.

00:38:28.920 --> 00:38:31.050
And we know you don't want
to degrade that experience by

00:38:31.050 --> 00:38:33.050
serving up poor quality ads.

00:38:33.170 --> 00:38:35.100
And that's where iAd comes in.

00:38:35.140 --> 00:38:38.300
iAd serves compelling, rich media ads.

00:38:38.350 --> 00:38:40.940
And it's now available in 14 countries.

00:38:41.190 --> 00:38:45.400
Just this week we launched in Taiwan,
Hong Kong, and Ireland to round it out.

00:38:46.410 --> 00:38:48.070
Now there's two aspects to iAd.

00:38:48.260 --> 00:38:51.260
There's the monetization
and there's the promotion.

00:38:51.350 --> 00:38:54.490
So let's begin by talking about
the monetization side of iAd

00:38:54.570 --> 00:38:58.520
and how you can leverage iAd to
generate revenue within your game.

00:38:58.700 --> 00:39:01.160
Well,
by serving up iAds within your game,

00:39:01.210 --> 00:39:05.380
you will receive a 70% revenue
share for every iAd that you serve.

00:39:05.690 --> 00:39:08.600
And the network is both
flexible and noncompetitive.

00:39:08.760 --> 00:39:11.340
What I mean is that while
you're serving iAds,

00:39:11.350 --> 00:39:15.800
you are still able to still go out
there and sell your own ads if you want.

00:39:15.930 --> 00:39:18.340
You also have the ability to
block your competitors from

00:39:18.430 --> 00:39:19.900
showing up within your game.

00:39:20.030 --> 00:39:23.890
So if you want to prevent certain apps
or certain brands from showing up,

00:39:23.890 --> 00:39:25.030
you can do that.

00:39:25.430 --> 00:39:29.800
As I said earlier,
iAd serves compelling rich media ads and

00:39:29.800 --> 00:39:31.790
you can track your results in real time.

00:39:31.950 --> 00:39:34.840
You can see the revenue, the taps,
the clicks that are occurring as

00:39:35.080 --> 00:39:36.320
they're occurring within your app.

00:39:36.380 --> 00:39:38.440
To get started, it's quite simple.

00:39:38.440 --> 00:39:41.630
Simply go into iTunes Connect,
fill out the iAd contract,

00:39:41.670 --> 00:39:44.180
implement the iAd
framework within your app,

00:39:44.180 --> 00:39:46.020
and then submit it for review.

00:39:46.020 --> 00:39:47.450
And you should be off and running.

00:39:49.420 --> 00:39:51.400
So that's the monetization side.

00:39:51.460 --> 00:39:54.440
Let's talk about the promotion
side and how you can leverage iAd

00:39:54.440 --> 00:39:56.770
to drive downloads of your apps.

00:39:57.120 --> 00:40:03.500
And for that, we introduced iAd Workbench
back at WWDC this past summer.

00:40:03.540 --> 00:40:07.660
iAd Workbench is a do-it-yourself
campaign creation and management tool.

00:40:07.710 --> 00:40:10.950
And when we announced it this summer,
it was available in the US only.

00:40:11.180 --> 00:40:14.020
But as of this week,
it's now available in all 14

00:40:14.100 --> 00:40:16.620
countries that I mentioned earlier.

00:40:17.280 --> 00:40:21.320
So I'm going to talk about campaign
creation and the analytics that we serve.

00:40:21.410 --> 00:40:24.680
So let's begin by talking
about the campaign creation.

00:40:25.850 --> 00:40:28.350
It takes just a couple of minutes
to get your campaign up and running.

00:40:28.350 --> 00:40:30.600
It's five simple steps.

00:40:30.730 --> 00:40:33.230
You must first, of course,
select the app you want to promote,

00:40:33.340 --> 00:40:35.140
which is your app.

00:40:35.580 --> 00:40:37.040
Then you need to select your audience.

00:40:37.090 --> 00:40:40.060
And for the non-marketers in the room,
it could not be simpler.

00:40:40.370 --> 00:40:43.890
By selecting automatic,
we will find the best audience

00:40:43.890 --> 00:40:48.260
for you based upon the integration
that iAd has with the App Store.

00:40:48.860 --> 00:40:52.360
But for the marketers that are out here,
you can do your own manual targeting.

00:40:52.400 --> 00:40:54.820
There's eight different
criteria you can select,

00:40:54.820 --> 00:40:58.420
whether it's gender, whether it's age,
whether it's region or

00:40:58.420 --> 00:41:00.210
interest within the App Store.

00:41:00.540 --> 00:41:03.320
You can do as much targeting as you want.

00:41:03.610 --> 00:41:08.060
The third step is to tell iAd how much
you want to spend over what period of

00:41:08.060 --> 00:41:10.000
time and then you upload your creative.

00:41:10.000 --> 00:41:14.230
Now if you don't have the creative
resources in your company to do this,

00:41:14.230 --> 00:41:16.530
we actually have four
templates that you can use,

00:41:16.530 --> 00:41:19.550
varying colors and fonts,
to make it look unique for yourself.

00:41:19.590 --> 00:41:23.100
And then you submit your campaign
and you'll get a response within 24

00:41:23.120 --> 00:41:25.060
hours and you'll be up and running.

00:41:26.620 --> 00:41:29.440
Now, once your campaign is running,
we provide a dashboard of analytics.

00:41:29.530 --> 00:41:33.880
We provide a macro view of the account
that allows you to monitor your

00:41:34.000 --> 00:41:35.990
campaigns but also initiate new ones.

00:41:35.990 --> 00:41:39.780
But then you can get into the detailed
statistics of the campaign if you want.

00:41:39.850 --> 00:41:42.200
You can look at specific time periods.

00:41:42.220 --> 00:41:45.290
You can look at your spend,
your impressions, your downloads,

00:41:45.290 --> 00:41:48.480
your taps, your tap-through rates,
and then your cost per click

00:41:48.480 --> 00:41:50.190
and your cost per acquisition.

00:41:50.200 --> 00:41:54.760
And you can also export this data
as a CSV file that you can import

00:41:54.820 --> 00:41:57.920
then into your own analytics package.

00:41:58.290 --> 00:42:02.640
